HEADWORD: lyophilized
<hw>lyophilized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>dried by freezing and
subsequent evaporation of the water in a high vacuum; -- used of tissue
or blood or serum or other biological or sensitive substances.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lyophilised, freeze-dried.</syn>⟦br⟧
